^SAMPLE = GSM8905195
!Sample_title = CITE-seq ADT library 1
!Sample_geo_accession = GSM8905195
!Sample_status = Public on Oct 10 2025
!Sample_submission_date = Apr 11 2025
!Sample_last_update_date = Oct 10 2025
!Sample_type = SRA
!Sample_channel_count = 1
!Sample_source_name_ch1 = PBMC
!Sample_organism_ch1 = Homo sapiens
!Sample_taxid_ch1 = 9606
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = tissue: PBMC
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = cell type: T cells
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = treatment: ATI
!Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1 = Longitudinal samples from a participant undergoing analytical treatment interruption.
!Sample_molecule_ch1 = protein
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = Epitope-specific CD8+ T cells were isolated by FACS.
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = 10x Genomics Chromium Next GEM Single Cell 5' Reagent Kit v2 (Dual Index) library construction protocol with feature barcodes
!Sample_description = Library name: ADT1
!Sample_description = ADT
!Sample_description = HEAL_FILTERED_ADT_COUNTS.tsv.gz
!Sample_description = HEAL_FILTERED_HTO_COUNTS.tsv.gz
!Sample_description = HEAL_FILTERED_TET_COUNTS.tsv.gz
!Sample_data_processing = Demultiplexing using bcl2fastq version 2.19.1.403 and the provided sample sheet.
!Sample_data_processing = CellRanger multianalysis specifying "Gene Expression", "Antibody Capture", and "VDJ-T" feature types with refdata-gex-GRCh38-2020-A as the genomic reference and refdata-cellranger-vdj-GRCh38-alts-ensembl-5.0.0 as the VDJ reference.
!Sample_data_processing = Seurat processing in R: counts from the "sample_filtered_feature_bc_matrix/matrix.mtx.gz" file generated by CellRanger were imported into R using the readMM() function from the Matrix package and used to construct a Seurat object for analysis. Demultiplexing of cells on the basis of hashtag oligos to assign cells to time points was performed using the HTODemux() function from Seurat. Samples corresponding to the top 5% of  counts for the A03_FLU_IK9 and A03_EBV_RK9 were removed from the data set because staining for those specificities was poor. TCR counts were imported from the "multi/vdj_t/filtered_contig_annotations.csv" file. For clustering, dimensionality reduction, differential expression, and other analysis, genes matching the following regular expression "^TR[ABDG][VJC]" were removed so that clustering would not be driven by clonotype-specific TCR gene expression. Only cells that were unambiguously assigned to a by HTO (HTO_classification.global == "Singlet") were included in the filtered data set.
!Sample_data_processing = Assembly: GRCh38-2020-A
!Sample_data_processing = Supplementary files format and content: tsv: tab separated values and tsv.gz: gzip-compressed tab-separated values.
!Sample_data_processing = Library strategy: CITE-seq
!Sample_platform_id = GPL30173
!Sample_contact_name = Jonathan,Morris,Urbach
!Sample_contact_email = jurbach@mgh.harvard.edu
!Sample_contact_laboratory = Walker
!Sample_contact_institute = Ragon Institute of MGH, MIT and Harvard
!Sample_contact_address = 400 Technology Sq Rm 851
!Sample_contact_city = Cambridge
!Sample_contact_state = Massachusetts
